stegfs: stegfs (a steganographic file system)
stegfs:
stegfs: stegfs is a FUSE based file system which provides absolute security.
stegfs: Using encryption to secure files, and the art of steganography to hide
stegfs: them, stegfs aims to ensure that the existence of such files isn't
stegfs: guaranteed. Implemented as a FUSE based file system and using the mhash
stegfs: and mcrypt libraries to provide the cryptographic hash and block cipher
stegfs: functions, stegfs is at the cutting edge of file system security.
stegfs: Dependencies: fuse mcrypt mhash
stegfs: It's likely your system already has all of these are they're included
stegfs: in the default Slackware installation.
